      <originalsloc id="aspace_75e7e7c1886a0f85fd5da0b733fea3d3">
         <head>Existence and Location of Originals</head>
         <p>The entire collection can be located in the The Thomas Davis Day Papers (MS 1674). The papers consist of fifteen letterbooks, which range in date from 1839 to 1871, a book recounting the history of the Day family,  written by Stanley M. Rowe, Jr. in 1990, and a scrapbook.</p>
         <p>HM 235 only consists of the letterbook volumes in boxes 1 to 3 of the original accession</p>  
      </originalsloc>
